Property Description: Sparse or Full Matrix of Double

The coefficients of the constraints of the metabolites.
The sense of the constraints represented by b, each row is either E (equality), L(less than) or G(greater than)

The objective coefficient of the reactions.
The objective sense either -1 for maximisation or 1 for minimisation

GPR rules in evaluateable format for each reaction ( e.g. "x(1) | x(2) & x(3)", would indicate the first gene or both the second and third gene are necessary for the respective reaction to carry flux

Symbols for compartments, can include Tissue information
Name of a file the model is loaded from.
